Mapping to top / htop
Now everything clicks.

CPU %
High CPU + slow app
→ Too many runnable threads
Moderate CPU + timeouts
→ Threads blocked (DB, I/O)


Load Average (CRITICAL)
Load average = Number of runnable + waiting threads

Rule of thumb:
Load ≈ CPU cores → healthy
Load >> CPU cores → saturation

This maps directly to CPU scheduling pressure.

Memory (RES)
Memory includes:
Stack memory (threads)
Heap memory (objects)
Kernel buffers (sockets)

Sudden growth?
→ Thread explosion or memory leak

Thread count
High thread count =
High stack memory usage
High scheduler overhead
Poor performance



